Create a Calculated Insight from a Package

Create a calculated insight from an installed Salesforce package in Data Cloud.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSION SETS
NEEDED
To create calculated insights:	Data Cloud Admin
In Data Cloud, go to the Calculated Insights tab, and click New.
From the Data Space dropdown, select a data space.
You can use only the data spaces that you have access to. Only the objects that are included in the data space are available to create a calculated insight.
Click Create from a Package, and then click Next.
Choose an installed package, and then click Next.
The Calculated Insight Name, Calculated Insight API Name, and SQL Query fields are auto-filled.
Click Save and Run.

You can view your insight on the record home page. After it’s created, you can’t edit the calculated insight. However, if it has no dependencies, you can delete it from the package.
